In another aspect, the invention relates to the use of an isolated peptide or polypeptide comprising a peptide or polypeptide with a sequence selected from the group consisting of:
(a) a sequence as disclosed in SEQ ID NO. 2, 4;
(b) a sequence that exhibits a sequence identity with any of the sequences according to (a) of at least 70 % over 100 residues;
(c) fragments of the sequences defined in (a) or (b), wherein the fragments are encoded by fragments of the nucleic acid sequences as defined above, for use in the activation of cell cycle progression for the treatment of a disease characterized by increased apoptosis, growth retardation, or slowed wound healing.
